title: Google\Cloud\Vision\V1\FaceAnnotation
name: FaceAnnotation
description:
A face annotation object contains the results of face detection.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.vision.v1.FaceAnnotation

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.bounding_poly
params.description: The bounding polygon around the face. The coordinates of the bounding box are in the original image's scale. The bounding box is computed to "frame" the face in accordance with human expectations. It is based on the landmarker results. Note that one or more x and/or y coordinates may not be generated in the BoundingPoly (the polygon will be unbounded) if only a partial face appears in the image to be annotated.

params.name: data.fd_bounding_poly
params.description: The fd_bounding_poly bounding polygon is tighter than the boundingPoly, and encloses only the skin part of the face. Typically, it is used to eliminate the face from any image analysis that detects the "amount of skin" visible in an image. It is not based on the landmarker results, only on the initial face detection, hence the fd (face detection) prefix.

params.name: data.roll_angle
params.description: Roll angle, which indicates the amount of clockwise/anti-clockwise rotation of the face relative to the image vertical about the axis perpendicular to the face. Range [-180,180].

params.name: data.pan_angle
params.description: Yaw angle, which indicates the leftward/rightward angle that the face is pointing relative to the vertical plane perpendicular to the image. Range [-180,180].

params.name: data.tilt_angle
params.description: Pitch angle, which indicates the upwards/downwards angle that the face is pointing relative to the image's horizontal plane. Range [-180,180].
